{"id":"4904","name":"Shazam to Spotify","tagline":"Identifies the currently playing song and adds it to a Spotify playlist","icon":"ios13 c4292093695 g59753","latest":"15774","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Shazam → Spotify</h2>\n<p>This shortcut is an easy way to let Shazam identify the currently playing song and add it to a predefined Spotify playlist.</p>\n<p>Until today Spotify doesn't really offer any useful shortcut support. Adding songs to a personal Spotify playlist is quite cumbersome when using their official web API. That's why I chose to use <a href=\"https://ifttt.com\"><strong>IFTTT</strong> </a> for that purpose which makes the whole process a lot easier.</p>\n<p>You need to create a little IFTTT webhook in order to make this shortcut work:\n</p><ul>\n<li> Login to your IFTTT account</li>\n<li> Click on your profile picture (upper right) and select \"Create\"</li>\n<li> If → click the \"+\" icon → choose \"Webhooks\" → Receive a web request → name it \"add_track_to_spotify\" → Then → Spotify → Add track to a playlist: </li>\n<code>Playlist name → click \"Add Ingredient\" → choose Value1</code><br>\n<code>Search query → click \"Add Ingredient\" → choose Value2</code><br>\n<code>Artist name → click \"Add Ingredient\" → choose Value3</code><br><p></p>\n<p><strong>Preview:</strong> It should look like this</p>\n<p><img alt=\"screenshot\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gommOFo.png\"></p><p>\n</p></ul><p></p>\n<p><strong>To obtain your IFTTT webhook key:</strong></p>\n<p>on IFTTT click on your profile picture (upper right) → My Services → choose Webhooks → Settings (upper right) → The key is the last part of the URL, in my case <strong>2LbE...</strong>, see:</p>\n<p><img alt=\"screenshot\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/2lEzmJS.png\"></p><p></p>\n<p>→ This key is needed for this shortcut and the import wizard asks for this key upon installation.</p>\n<p><strong>Shortcut preview:</strong></p>\n<p><img alt=\"screenrecording\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/xkmxQlZ.mp4\"></p>